        public java.lang.String completeElement(java.lang.String elementId,
                               java.lang.String nodeId,
                               java.lang.String nextNodeId,
                               java.lang.String workerId,
                               java.lang.String gfsKey,
                               java.lang.String extra1,
                               java.lang.String extra2,
                               java.lang.String extra3,
                               int totalOuput,
                               int totalError)
        Parameters:
        elementId - = Element Id to Complete
        currentNodeId - = Node Id of where the element is in process
        nextNodeId - = Next Node Id of where the element will be transfered to continue processing
        workerId - = Worker Id of worker in next node
        filePointer - = Edit File Pointer
        extra1 - = Edit Extra1
        extra2 - = Edit Extra2
        extra3 - = Edit Extra3
        totalOuput - = Increment Output Count of Current Node
        totalError - = Increment Total Error Count of Current Node, Put 0 If Error Count not belongs to current node and Call:
        incrementNodeErrorCount(String nodeId, int errorCount), and put the nodeId of node who produced the error
        Returns:
        String Notification
